When using image files that are directly in assets/ folder (Android app), this code part in ResolutionFileResolver incorrectly prefixes the path with /, making it an absolute path:

``` java
protected String resolve (FileHandle originalHandle, String suffix) {
        return originalHandle.parent() + "/" + suffix + "/" + originalHandle.name();
}
```

In this case, originalHandle.parent() is empty string, which results into '/' being the first character in path.

When the images are placed inside a subfolder in assets, such as assets/img, everything works ok.

